{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Design doc written: docs/adr/0007-editing-prompt-contracts-from-the-editor.md + companion pointer in docs/workflow-authoring-v2.md §1.4. Decision: (1) prompt inputs/outputs schema NAMES editable via the existing 6592 prompt-save form with a registry pick-list + fail-closed write-time resolve-check; reuse (not re-solve) the existing prompt_override_drift gate by factoring its outputs-diff into a shared helper the editor calls at write time (block-then-confirm on breaking outputs-override); no schema_version bump / no new front-matter key. (2) scripted-op @register_step contracts NOT editable — code is the single source (no file artifact; import-time STEP_CONTRACTS; a runtime override would re-create the ADR-0006 view-vs-runtime divergence). Inline schemas explicitly out of scope. 6 follow-on stories identified. make lint green."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782781793078279001,"uuid":"a35020d7-6388-456c-811a-cb84c4383334"}